tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, marked proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low urine specific gravity and brown, cloudy urine. These findings suggest impaired renal function, likely chronic kidney disease with possible nephrotic-range proteinuria. The presence of glucosuria with low HbA1c and normal blood glucose may indicate renal glycosuria. Urine findings (color, appearance) may also suggest possible urinary tract pathology. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and further workup.
